{
  "stem": "11671.1",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When we went out we-- until we waited to be counted, we would hug each other to, to, to keep each other warm.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And before selection, my sister would pinch my cheeks to give me a little color.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So just basically, because we were together and we, we talked and we sang songs and we--",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We, we prayed and we sang songs from our youth, the-- all the Zionist songs, that we were going to go to, you know, to Palestine and build the land, and all the songs.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we would practice our Hebrew, because during our childhood, we, we studied Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And at day school, we had to learn how to read and write, but we weren't allowed to use it as a language, because it's a holy tongue.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You're not supposed to use it for speaking.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So in camp, we were practicing our Hebrew, because we wanted-- we knew we were going to Palestine when we were liberated.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we just kept our place clean, and we just-- and we really supported each other.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my sister realized that people-- they had selections constantly.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my sister saw that the selections, were not-- they weren't picking able-bodied people and real strong and healthy ones.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were picking weak people.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So my sister said, let's not rush to the selections.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So we, we held back so the Germans would say, OK, everybody out of the barrack.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then when everybody went out and they only took 500.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So we-- they didn't take everybody.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So we didn't rush to go out of the barrack, so we escaped many selections that way.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Auschwitz, we had one overseer who was a teacher from Hungary, from Cluj-- Kolozsvar, the same city.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she helped the German overseer.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
